do you have api to import data

Yes, we do have an API for importing data. You can integrate our API with your application to enable seamless data exchange and automation. To get started, you'll need to create an ad account and request your token. For detailed instructions, please refer to our API Integration Guide here: [API Integration Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/27680147056397-API-Integration-Guide). If you encounter any issues, feel free to contact adsupport@newsbreak.com.

Impression pixels are used to track when an ad is displayed to users on a platform. They help measure the reach and exposure of your campaigns. If you need more detailed information on setting up impression tracking, you can refer to our article on App Install Events which includes sample URLs for impression tracking. Here's the link: [Introduction to App Install Events](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/26530008151309-Introduction-to-App-Install-Events). Let me know if you have any other questions!
